A function \( f(x) \) is said to have a ${BBOLD}jump$EBOLD 
discontinuity at \(x=a\) if all three of the following conditions hold:
    \{BeginList("OL")\}
    $ITEM
        \( \displaystyle{\lim_{x\to a^-}f(x)} \) exists.
    $ITEMSEP

    $ITEM
        \( \displaystyle{\lim_{x\to a^+}f(x)} \) exists.
    $ITEMSEP

    $ITEM
       The left and right limits are not equal.
    \{EndList("OL")\}
$PAR
